[
    {
        "text": "Hi, I’m Francis, ",
        "start": 6.544,
        "duration": 1.234
    },
    {
        "text": "the host of this show \"Cooking with Dog.\"",
        "start": 7.778,
        "duration": 2.842
    },
    {
        "text": "First, let’s make the potato filling.",
        "start": 16.637,
        "duration": 2.921
    },
    {
        "text": "Soak the peeled Japanese sweet potato ",
        "start": 19.772,
        "duration": 2.878
    },
    {
        "text": "in a generous amount of water for about 10 minutes ",
        "start": 22.65,
        "duration": 3.66
    },
    {
        "text": "to reduce any unwanted flavors.",
        "start": 26.31,
        "duration": 2.882
    },
    {
        "text": "Strain the potato and place it into a pot of water.",
        "start": 29.624,
        "duration": 4.357
    },
    {
        "text": "Heat it on low heat.",
        "start": 34.644,
        "duration": 2.033
    },
    {
        "text": "Gradually heating the potato ",
        "start": 37.41,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "will help to increase its sweetness.",
        "start": 39.33,
        "duration": 3.003
    },
    {
        "text": "Cook until it softens and slightly crumbles.",
        "start": 45.6,
        "duration": 3.901
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, strain the potato thoroughly.",
        "start": 53.76,
        "duration": 2.966
    },
    {
        "text": "Place it into a bowl.",
        "start": 62.395,
        "duration": 1.981
    },
    {
        "text": "When it is still hot, add the salt ",
        "start": 65.464,
        "duration": 3.084
    },
    {
        "text": "and sugar.",
        "start": 70.681,
        "duration": 1.467
    },
    {
        "text": "Mash the potato with a masher.",
        "start": 75.181,
        "duration": 2.922
    },
    {
        "text": "The sweetness varies depending on the type of potato ",
        "start": 78.446,
        "duration": 3.672
    },
    {
        "text": "so adjust the amount of sugar accordingly. ",
        "start": 82.118,
        "duration": 3.107
    },
    {
        "text": "Thoroughly mix to combine.",
        "start": 93.493,
        "duration": 2.169
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, place the potato filling into a mold ",
        "start": 101.88,
        "duration": 3.185
    },
    {
        "text": "covered with plastic wrap.",
        "start": 105.065,
        "duration": 2.334
    },
    {
        "text": "If the filling is too soft, ",
        "start": 109.517,
        "duration": 2.017
    },
    {
        "text": "microwave it to reduce the water ",
        "start": 111.534,
        "duration": 2.302
    },
    {
        "text": "before placing it in the container.",
        "start": 113.836,
        "duration": 2.702
    },
    {
        "text": "Shape the potato into a rectangle ",
        "start": 117.339,
        "duration": 2.466
    },
    {
        "text": "about 4x4x14cm (1.6\"x1.6\"x5.5”).",
        "start": 119.805,
        "duration": 3.835
    },
    {
        "text": "Cover with the plastic wrap.",
        "start": 126.458,
        "duration": 2.351
    },
    {
        "text": "Adjust the shape with a scraper ",
        "start": 130.028,
        "duration": 2.1
    },
    {
        "text": "to make it more presentable.",
        "start": 132.128,
        "duration": 2.69
    },
    {
        "text": "Chill the potato filling in the fridge or freezer ",
        "start": 134.976,
        "duration": 3.122
    },
    {
        "text": "until the inside is firm.",
        "start": 138.098,
        "duration": 2.519
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, let’s make the batter for the wrapper.",
        "start": 143.217,
        "duration": 3.472
    },
    {
        "text": "Add a small amount of water to ",
        "start": 147.103,
        "duration": 1.95
    },
    {
        "text": "the shiratamako or mochiko, sweet rice flour.",
        "start": 149.053,
        "duration": 4.584
    },
    {
        "text": "Mix thoroughly.",
        "start": 154.755,
        "duration": 2.302
    },
    {
        "text": "When the clumps of flour have disappeared, ",
        "start": 157.225,
        "duration": 3.065
    },
    {
        "text": "add the rest of the water.",
        "start": 160.29,
        "duration": 2.168
    },
    {
        "text": "Mix again.",
        "start": 163.743,
        "duration": 1.566
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, add the cake flour ",
        "start": 168.6,
        "duration": 2.434
    },
    {
        "text": "and a pinch of salt.",
        "start": 171.543,
        "duration": 1.961
    },
    {
        "text": "Combine the mixture evenly.",
        "start": 176.685,
        "duration": 2.653
    },
    {
        "text": "The batter should be relatively thin as Chef is showing here.",
        "start": 183.879,
        "duration": 4.697
    },
    {
        "text": "Next, cut the chilled potato filling ",
        "start": 192.211,
        "duration": 2.601
    },
    {
        "text": "into 2cm (0.8”) thick slices.",
        "start": 194.812,
        "duration": 3.132
    },
    {
        "text": "Dampen the knife for each cut ",
        "start": 198.764,
        "duration": 2.018
    },
    {
        "text": "to help make a clean cut.",
        "start": 200.782,
        "duration": 2.384
    },
    {
        "text": "You’ll have 7 pieces in total.",
        "start": 203.694,
        "duration": 2.967
    },
    {
        "text": "And now, let’s make the kintsuba.",
        "start": 207.962,
        "duration": 2.684
    },
    {
        "text": "Heat a pan on medium heat ",
        "start": 210.862,
        "duration": 2.253
    },
    {
        "text": "and coat it with vegetable oil using a paper towel.",
        "start": 213.115,
        "duration": 4.034
    },
    {
        "text": "Dip one side of the square surface into the batter.",
        "start": 218.465,
        "duration": 3.725
    },
    {
        "text": "Sprinkle the toasted black sesame seeds on the center.",
        "start": 222.465,
        "duration": 4.503
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, place it onto the pan and lightly press it.",
        "start": 226.968,
        "duration": 4.037
    },
    {
        "text": "Repeat the process for the rest of the pieces.",
        "start": 231.906,
        "duration": 3.567
    },
    {
        "text": "When the batter is dry, ",
        "start": 238.413,
        "duration": 1.681
    },
    {
        "text": "remove and dip the other side into the batter.",
        "start": 240.094,
        "duration": 3.933
    },
    {
        "text": "Place it onto the pan.",
        "start": 245.462,
        "duration": 2.318
    },
    {
        "text": "Repeat the process for the rest of the kintsuba ",
        "start": 251.749,
        "duration": 2.868
    },
    {
        "text": "and lightly press them again.",
        "start": 254.617,
        "duration": 2.623
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, the top and bottom are ready.",
        "start": 259.386,
        "duration": 2.767
    },
    {
        "text": "Repeat the process for the rest of the 4 sides.",
        "start": 262.737,
        "duration": 3.74
    },
    {
        "text": "They are hot so be sure to use a kitchen glove ",
        "start": 272.86,
        "duration": 3.066
    },
    {
        "text": "or spatula to avoid burning yourself.",
        "start": 275.926,
        "duration": 3.318
    },
    {
        "text": "Place each kintsuba onto a cooling rack ",
        "start": 285.718,
        "duration": 2.928
    },
    {
        "text": "as soon as it is ready, ",
        "start": 288.646,
        "duration": 2.036
    },
    {
        "text": "When the wrapper of the leftover kintsuba ",
        "start": 293.783,
        "duration": 2.401
    },
    {
        "text": "has become firm, try deep-frying them.",
        "start": 296.184,
        "duration": 3.499
    },
    {
        "text": "They are also delicious ",
        "start": 299.683,
        "duration": 1.669
    },
    {
        "text": "and you’ll enjoy a different, crisp texture.",
        "start": 301.352,
        "duration": 3.385
    },
    {
        "text": "Depending on the type of sweet potato, ",
        "start": 311.107,
        "duration": 2.583
    },
    {
        "text": "the water content may vary.",
        "start": 313.69,
        "duration": 1.958
    },
    {
        "text": "If the filling is too dry, ",
        "start": 315.648,
        "duration": 2.058
    },
    {
        "text": "add boiled milk to adjust the consistency.",
        "start": 317.706,
        "duration": 3.811
    },
    {
        "text": "Good luck in the kitchen!",
        "start": 321.517,
        "duration": 17.255
    }
]